1. The prevention and control of epidemic situation in China has entered a decisive stage, and all imported cases have been isolated

Summary of China Today: 80,552 cases were reported in China on March 5,143 new cases, lower than Italy, Iran, South Korea, Germany and other countries. There were 126 new cases from Wuhan, only 1 case from non-wuhan area and 16 cases imported from abroad. These imported cases have been quarantined for the first time after entry and there is little chance of further spread within the country. Hubei non-wuhan region achieves zero new growth for the first time. At the same time, the vast non-wuhan areas have completely encircled the epidemic situation in Wuhan, and the fight against the epidemic in China has reached a decisive point. Considering that the overall epidemic situation abroad is still in the early stage of epidemic, and that a longer period of time and larger-scale development may be unavoidable, and in accordance with the request of the central government, "to accelerate the establishment of an economic and social operational order corresponding to the prevention and control of epidemic situations" , "strive to national economic and social development into the normal track as soon as possible" has become an inevitable choice.
